Media relay for SIP VoIP calls

Mediaproxy is a media relay server for the OpenSER SIP proxy that handles
NAT traversal for media streams from user agents behind NAT and has the
following features:

 - Distributed geographical location
 - Scalability, load balancing and redundancy
 - Real-time sessions statistics
 - Configurable IP and UDP port range
 - Support for audio and video streams
 - Support for multiple media streams per call
 - Accounting of network traffic

Mediaproxy is meant to be used together with OpenSER's mediaproxy module.
